@chickenlj The **SOLUTION** I proposed doesn't break the immutability of `URL`, the proposed `URLBuilder` is used to reduce the **middle state objects** when building a new `URL` from an old one.

```java
new URL("dubbo", NetUtils.getLocalHost(), port, RegistryService.class.getName()) // useless middle state URL
                        .setPath(RegistryService.class.getName()) // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter(Constants.INTERFACE_KEY, RegistryService.class.getName()) // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter(Constants.CLUSTER_STICKY_KEY, "true") // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter(Constants.CALLBACK_INSTANCES_LIMIT_KEY, "1000") // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter("ondisconnect", "disconnect") // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter("subscribe.1.callback", "true") // useless middle state URL
                        .addParameter("unsubscribe.1.callback", "false")));
```

produces 7 useless `URL` objects, and

```java
new URLBuilder("dubbo", NetUtils.getLocalHost(), port, RegistryService.class.getName())
                        .setPath(RegistryService.class.getName())
                        .addParameter(Constants.INTERFACE_KEY, RegistryService.class.getName())
                        .addParameter(Constants.CLUSTER_STICKY_KEY, "true")
